# Cursor Project Rules

## ⛔ AUTO-GENERATED FILES — DO NOT EDIT

The following directories contain auto-generated build output. **Never edit
these files directly.** They are overwritten every time the deploy script
(`scripts/push-to-github.command`) runs.

| Path | What it is | How it's generated |
|---|---|---|
| `docs/` | GitHub Pages deploy target | rsync'd from `webapp/out/` |
| `docs/**/*.html` | Static HTML pages | Next.js static export |
| `docs/**/*.css` | Compiled stylesheets | Tailwind + Next.js build |
| `docs/**/*.js` | Client-side bundles | Next.js build |
| `docs/**/*.txt` | RSC payloads | Next.js build |
| `webapp/out/` | Next.js static export output | `npm run build` (gitignored) |
| `webapp/.next/` | Next.js build cache | `npm run build` (gitignored) |

### Build pipeline

```
webapp/src/  ──(npm run build)──▸  webapp/out/  ──(rsync)──▸  docs/  ──(git push)──▸  GitHub Pages
  (source)                        (build output)              (deploy target)         (live site)
```

### Where to make changes

- **All code edits** go in `webapp/src/` (components, pages, CSS, data, etc.)
- **Static assets** (images, icons, fonts) go in `webapp/public/`
- **Project data** lives in `webapp/src/data/` — or re-run `npm run extract`
- The root-level `.html` files (`index.html`, `about.html`, etc.) and
  `assets/css/styles.css` are **legacy fallback pages** and are not part of the
  Next.js build pipeline.

